 Confluence, SFDC, Outreach, and a number of other tools), and look forward to refining, improving, and augmenting those systems to continue to drive performance and growth. In the short term, you\u2019ll: Listen and learn: you\u2019ll become fluent in our product, value propositions, who our customers are, their problems we\u2019re solving, and our competitive landscape. Iterate on the existing editorial calendar and execute across multiple platforms, including website, blog, webinars, videos, newsletters, social media, PR, copywriting, email, partner and customer content marketing, and case studies. Develop plans and tactics for increasing new marketing-qualified opportunities through content, integrating these with the overall strategy. Begin to execute individually on content, incorporating first-party data and research. Manage content partners, ensuring they meet key deadlines and produce high-value deliverables. In the longer term, you\u2019ll: Develop and own the Intricately content strategy to drive customer acquisition and customer success. Work closely with the Customer Success, Product, and Sales Team to establish customer marketing and highly relevant content marketing. Own and report on the content performance metrics and hold the marketing team accountable to milestones and objectives. Lead, manage, and grow a team of content contractors and vendors Be able to tell a data-rich story on how you\u2019ve impacted the marketing funnel at Intricately. You have: At least 5+ years of experience in content marketing for technology-based companies. A deep understanding of B2B technology (bonus for direct experience with a technical / Data-as-a-Service offering). An adept and experienced storyteller who can collaborate across a wide variety of functions to deliver data-driven analysis through content. A track record of experience across long/short-form content, video development, brand copy, webinars, social media, newsletters, and digital marketing copy. Understanding, experience, and/or strong opinions about key metrics and tools like Google Analytics and Hubspot to monitor content engagement. Familiarity with modern content marketing best practices and tools. Excellent writing and editorial skills; proven ability to think strategically and execute methodically with strong attention to detail. Solid command of SEO, SEM, and inbound marketing best practices. Experience managing and owning an editorial calendar in a collaboration tool Excellent people management and teamwork skills including working with vendors and contractors to produce the best content. A \u201cteam player\u201d attitude, willingness to support others and ask for help, ability to lead in ambiguous situations, and confidence to admit the things you know you don\u2019t know. What you get: Competitive salary Comprehensive medical, dental and vision insurance Stock options 401k with employer match Whatever computer and desk setup you want \u2013 let\u2019s get to work! Intricately is an equal opportunity employer. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, or disability status. We\u2019re proud to welcome people with different backgrounds, perspectives, and experiences \u2014 join us and let\u2019s make something awesome together. Apply for job Apply for job If this job interests you but you aren\u2019t certain if you meet all of the\u00c2\u00a0requirements, apply anyway! More Jobs Website Twitter Or view all jobs: Developer jobs Marketing jobs Product jobs Design jobs Sales jobs Support jobs & learn about: remote work Related Jobs Marketing Manager \u2013 Ecosystem SmartContract Smart Contracts are self-executing contractual states, stored on the blockchain, which nobody controls and therefore everyone can trust. Anywhere Full Time Posted 3 weeks ago Content Editor Aha! The World's #1 Product Roadmap & Marketing Planning Anywhere Full Time Posted 4 weeks ag